{"TopicId":85996,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do you turn a Kerbal upside down on EVA?","CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-03T19:16:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-03T19:16:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have heard of the glitch where Kerbals can survive a long fall if they land on their helmet. But I can\u0027t seem to flip a Kerbal upside down with the jet pack. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHow do I do it?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-03T19:17:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EClick and drag on the Kerbal.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cerberus738","CreatedById":100744,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-04T19:01:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou can also try switching camera view to orbital. It should flip the Kerbal relative to the surface. Pretty sure it\u0027s a glitch though\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-05T21:48:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks a lot!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Engineer of Stuff","CreatedById":106757,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-05T21:53:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks a lot!\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}